, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"text" : "The parse message thing acts like a kind of dynamic route object : the message header is used as an internal target, and the value that follows the header is forwarded to the target.\nAdvantages : \n- you can add any \"#0-paramname\" receive object in your patch, and it will be accessible via a \"paramname\" message\n- you can set a default value for any named parameter via attributes (\"@paramname value\")\n- it might be a little bit less efficient than using patchchords, but more efficient than using route objects\n- some will certainly hate it...",
